				\begin{document}$$\upzeta$$\end{document}= 4.86%). On the other hand, the simulated transparency of sample #4 is not considered the maximum reported transparency, but it is only 3% away from the maximum transparency showed by sample #6 (88.44% to 85.59%). Similar behavior is also detected in the other two sources, LED and Xenon lamps. As a result, sample #4 can be nominated as the best sample among those under test in performing semi-transparent light-harvesting capabilities.
